      "created": "2015-06-16T04:04:41.952+0000",
      "description": "This proposal talks about the issues of YARN fair scheduling policy, and tries to solve them by YARN-3806 and the new scheduling policy called time extended fair scheduling.\n\nTime extended fair scheduling policy is proposed to enforces fairness over time among users. For example, if two users share the cluster weekly, each user\u2019s fair share is half of the cluster per week. At a particular week, if the first user has used the whole cluster for first half of the week, then in second half of the week, second user will always have priority to use cluster resources since the first user has used up its time extended fair share of the cluster already.",
